  "market_context": "Bearish-bias week on BLL daily where Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday opposed the intended weekly direction. Wednesday formed a potential high of week but did not produce a clean candle 2 closure, leaving the reversal unconfirmed on Wednesday's close.",
  "key_observation": "Wednesday lacked a clean candle 2 closure, but Thursday delivered a candle 3 closure and change in state of delivery, confirming Wednesday as the high of the week and enabling a Friday continuation lower into failure swings.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Observed a swing point forming and asked whether the next candle would expand higher (reversal) or form a new reversal candle indicating retracement to continue lower.",
    "Step 2: Noted price took out a small prior high but did not produce a clean candle 2 closure on Wednesday, only a reversal-looking candle suggesting expansion-into-retracement to continue lower.",
    "Step 3: Considered dropping to lower time frames for confirmation but preferred to wait for the higher time frame closure rather than trade Wednesday's unclean signal.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to the 1H chart on Thursday — entry there was possible but not super clean, so the analyst opted to let the daily Thursday candle close.",
    "Step 5: Thursday closed as a candle 3 closure with a change in state of delivery, confirming Wednesday as the high of the week.",
    "Step 6: Looked for Friday continuation lower, targeting failure swings sitting below the range.",
    "Step 7: Stepped back to the daily weekly profile: expansion, retracement, new expansion — Mon/Tue/Wed oppose the weekly range, Thursday confirms, Friday delivers continuation lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Friday delivered the anticipated continuation lower, running into the failure-swing lows below the range.",
  "lessons": "Weekly profiles are not always picture perfect; when Wednesday lacks a clean candle 2 closure and V-shape reversal, wait for Thursday's candle 3 closure and change in state of delivery to confirm the high of week before trading Friday continuation.",
